summary: This is an email notification from the DOJ's E2 travel system indicating a final travel voucher is pending approval for an FBI trip to Stockholm, Sweden in February 2020. The trip was related to the Epstein investigation for witness interviews.

events.title: FBI travel to Stockholm for Epstein investigation
events.description: FBI personnel traveled to Stockholm, Sweden for witness interviews related to the Epstein investigation (case 2018R01618).

keyFacts: The FBI conducted witness interviews in Stockholm, Sweden in February 2020 as part of the Epstein investigation (case 2018R01618).
The travel voucher shows expenses of $2,143.49 with an estimated total trip cost of $2,954.54.
The document indicates ongoing investigative activity in the Epstein case as of February 2020.
The travel was authorized under case reference R20NYS13340 - Epstein investigation (2018R01618).
